e-infra.prizm\n- src/routes -> .prizm-docs/src/routes.prizm\n- src/security -> .prizm-docs/src/security.prizm\n- src/services -> .prizm-docs/src/services.prizm\n- src/utils -> .prizm-docs/src/utils.prizm\n- public -> (static web panel assets — no L1 doc)\n\nRULES:\n- All chat messages route through messageRouter.processMessage() — never call executeAiCli directly for chat\n- Session keys: bound sessions use telegram:{chatId}, unbound web sessions use web:{sessionId}\n- Safe-to-modify config keys: LOG_LEVEL, REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS, AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_MS, MAX_PROMPT_CHARS, MAX_HISTORY_TURNS, SYSTEM_MONITOR_INTERVAL_MS, SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS, TASK_DEBOUNCE_MS\n- ANSI stripping happens in onAssistantChunk hook via ansiProcessChunk() — never strip in final reply path\n- Web panel CSS z-index hierarchy: .app-header=10, command-dropdown=100, lightbox=200, toast=300; details in CLAUDE.md\n- Web panel CSS modifier pattern: .status/.message/.output-box/.toast use modifier classes for state (connected/error/exit-error/success/info); dark mode overrides hardcoded light-palette values; details in CLAUDE.md\n- Dark mode via @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) in styles.css; :root color-scheme is `light dark`; hardcoded #fff backgrounds overridden to var(--panel)\n- CSS breakpoints: 900px collapses grids; 600px mobile layout (flex-wrap header, full-width buttons, reduced padding)\n- Toast: showToast(msg, type) in public/js/main.js; type='success'|'error'|'info'; auto-dismisses 3s + 300ms fade-out animation\n- Lightbox: openLightbox(src)/closeLightbox() in public/js/main.js; close on backdrop click (event.target !== img) or Esc keydown\n- Spinner: setBusy(busy, text, activeBtn?) in public/js/main.js; adds .loading to activeBtn when busy; removes from all buttons when idle; .btn.loading uses ::before pseudo-element with color: transparent on button text\n- Kbd hints: .kbd class (monospace, border-bottom-width:2px, rounded, --panel bg, --muted color) used inline next to buttons; wrapper divs .chat-form-actions/.exec-form-actions (flex, align-items:center) hold button+kbd pairs; .kbd uses only CSS vars so dark mode auto-switches without explicit override\n\nUPDATED: 2026-03-23\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":30,"oldLines":5,"newStart":30,"newLines":6,"lines":[" - Lightbox: openLightbox(src)/closeLightbox() in public/js/main.js; close on backdrop click (event.target !== img) or Esc keydown"," - Spinner: setBusy(busy, text, activeBtn?) in public/js/main.js; adds .loading to activeBtn when busy; removes from all buttons when idle; .btn.loading uses ::before pseudo-element with color: transparent on button text"," - Kbd hints: .kbd class (monospace, border-bottom-width:2px, rounded, --panel bg, --muted color) used inline next to buttons; wrapper divs .chat-form-actions/.exec-form-actions (flex, align-items:center) hold button+kbd pairs; .kbd uses only CSS vars so dark mode auto-switches without explicit override","+- Empty state: .empty-state component (flex column, centered, CSS vars only) inside #chatMessages and .exec-result; updateChatEmptyState() checks .message.user/.message.assistant only (system msgs don't count); updateExecEmptyState(hasResult) toggles #execEmptyState and #execOutput wrapper; clearChatBtn must re-append #chatEmptyState after innerHTML='' before next appendMessage call"," "," UPDATED: 2026-03-23"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
